The CLI script needs to accept three positional paths (data, model output, and histogram output) and compute baseline feature statistics. You must format the baseline JSON structure with stringified feature indices as keys, mapping to arrays for counts and boundaries. It is critical that the total items captured across bins strictly sums to exactly the input sample length of the training CSV to avoid dropping trailing edges.

For the Django backend endpoints, your prediction and batch drift endpoints must return standard REST HTTP 400 responses if inputs are malformed (e.g., if a request payload lacks the expected list of dictionary objects structure). The returned predictions and drift metrics must compute Population Stability Index (PSI) against the saved training baseline statistics and ensure PSI calculations are numerically robust against missing or empty intervals. Additionally, the returned prediction schemas must map prediction responses to standard keys, and the drift metrics payload must distinctly index metrics by stringified feature integer IDs.
